LEISUREAIR
PASSENGER SAFETY INFORMATION
If you are sitting in an exit row and you cannot read this card or cannot see well enough to follow these
instructions, please tell a crew member.
SEGURIDAD
Si usted se encuentra sentado/a en una fila de asientos a la par de una salida u usted no entiende el
idioma ingles, favor de avisarle a un tripulante.
Federal Regulations require that persons seated in an exit row be capable of physically opening the exit.
These exits are often heavy, awkward to lift, push, pull, and maneuver when opening
If you are seated in a designated exit row, you may be called upon to assist the crew in an emergency to
perform the following:
- Locate, recognize and operate an emergency exit.
Assess conditions outside an exit to determine safe egress.
Follow oral directions and hand signals given by a crew member.
Stow or secure the emergency exit door so it will not impede use of the exit.
Assess the condition of, activate and stabilize an escape slide to assist others in evacuating.
Pass expeditiously through an exit, assess, select, and follow a safe path away from exit.
No passenger may be seated in a designated exit row if it is likely they are unable to perform one or more
of the above functions because:
- Person lacks sufficient mobility, strength, or dexterity in both arms and hands, and both legs.
Person is less than 15 years of age.
Person cannot read or understand instructions provided related to emergency evacuation or
understand oral crew commands.
Person cannot see or hear well enough to perform one or more of the applicable functions
Person cannot give oral commands to others.
Person has other responsibilities such as caring for a small child.
Person has a condition that might cause them harm if they perform one or more of the functions.
If you are seated adjacent to an emergency exit, cannot or do not wish to assist in an emergency, please
identify yourself to a Flight Attendant.
